import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of S&P 500 index prices over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of S&P 500 index prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(['KDE'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['price'])
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average price of the S&P 500 index?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
